Definition: emphasize by putting heavy stress on or by moving to the front of the sentence
Example: Speakers topicalize more often than they realize; The object of the sentence is topicalized in what linguists call `Yiddish Movement'
Synonyms: noun, communication, topicalization, emphasize, cognition, linguistics, c, by, putting, heavy, stress, on, or, moving, to, the, front, of, sentence, Speakers, more, often, than, they, realize, The, object, is, topicalized, in, what, linguists, call, Yiddish, Movement
Frame: 2,8
Category: verb.communication
